WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.867
NARRATOR:
Previously on Smallville:

00:04.046 --> 00:06.002
DAVIS:
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

00:06.173 --> 00:08.835
I have hurt many people...

00:10.552 --> 00:11.678
...that I care about.

00:11.845 --> 00:15.713
No more than three tablets a day.
They can be highly addictive.

00:15.891 --> 00:19.008
Please, for your own good,
get out of here now.

00:19.353 --> 00:20.433
[DAVIS SCREAMS]

00:20.604 --> 00:21.593
[SCREAMS]

00:21.772 --> 00:24.434
JIMMY: I've put up with years
of you taking someone else's side.

00:24.608 --> 00:25.597
First Clark, then Davis?

00:25.776 --> 00:28.267
Marrying you was the biggest mistake
of my life.

00:28.445 --> 00:30.527
TESS:
There is a savior among us.

00:30.698 --> 00:32.279
Until you fulﬁll your destiny...

00:33.117 --> 00:35.449
...he won't have his great challenge
to overcome.

00:36.078 --> 00:37.943
You are destined to kill each other.

00:39.623 --> 00:41.739
Sorry about being
the invisible best friend.

00:41.917 --> 00:44.283
Just when I'd hit
my ﬁll of high-maintenance men...

00:44.461 --> 00:45.792
...I take a job from Oliver.

00:45.963 --> 00:48.955
Watchtower is ofﬁcially online.

00:49.633 --> 00:51.464
Something about being around you...

00:51.635 --> 00:54.126
...that seems to calm
the murderer inside me.

00:54.304 --> 00:55.430
Will you stay with me?

00:57.307 --> 01:00.640
PRIEST:
We all have our inner demons...

01:03.981 --> 01:07.098
...but we must learn to control them.

01:18.328 --> 01:20.319
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:30.466 --> 01:32.297
Davis, is everything okay?

01:32.468 --> 01:34.504
DAVIS [OVER PHONE]:
I'm sony ifl woke you.

01:34.678 --> 01:37.135
I had another one.

01:37.681 --> 01:41.549
It's just a dream.
You know you're safe with me.

01:41.727 --> 01:43.718
DAVIS [OVER PHONE]:
Could you come down anyway?

01:43.896 --> 01:45.602
Uh, [need to see you.

01:45.773 --> 01:49.186
Of course. I'll be down right away.

02:33.070 --> 02:36.938
You know, this isn't exactly
the typical response to a bad dream.

02:37.115 --> 02:38.821
Most people just get a night light.

02:38.992 --> 02:40.107
[CH UCKLES]

02:40.285 --> 02:41.991
I wanted to surprise you.

02:43.872 --> 02:44.907
It's beautiful.

02:46.750 --> 02:50.493
But I don't remember ever
seeing a box of candles down here.

02:50.671 --> 02:51.911
Or ﬂowers.

02:52.923 --> 02:54.709
There weren't any.

02:57.094 --> 03:00.086
Davis, we talked about this.

03:00.264 --> 03:03.006
-You can't leave the basement.
-I was careful.

03:03.559 --> 03:06.346
I know how much you're risking.
| only wanted to thank you.

03:06.520 --> 03:09.102
I don't need thanks.
I need to be able to trust you.

03:09.273 --> 03:11.434
I won't do it again. I'm sorry.

03:17.781 --> 03:24.027
Aah. Chloe, you've helped me
when no one else would.

03:24.788 --> 03:27.029
Well, friends help each other, right?

03:29.793 --> 03:31.579
Friends help you move...

03:31.753 --> 03:35.871
...they take you to the airport.
You can't think that's really all this is.

03:39.136 --> 03:42.628
Okay, so maybe it was a 9.9
on the Richter scale of favors, Davis...

03:42.806 --> 03:45.764
-...but that doesn't change our relationship.
-Chloe...

03:45.934 --> 03:49.973
...we met in a ﬂurry of smoking ash
and bumt—out cars, people freaking out...

03:50.147 --> 03:52.229
...but for a moment there...

03:52.608 --> 03:56.146
...it felt like everything disappeared
except us.

03:58.322 --> 03:59.812
Those feelings haven't changed.

04:04.453 --> 04:07.069
I do care about you, Davis.

04:08.498 --> 04:10.910
-But--
-Stay.

04:11.168 --> 04:12.157
Please.

04:15.005 --> 04:19.374
Without you,
the man that I wanna be doesn't exist.

05:11.561 --> 05:14.428
Davis, is that blood?

05:19.820 --> 05:22.106
What did you think was gonna happen?

05:51.935 --> 05:53.345
[GASPS]

05:55.397 --> 05:56.762
No.

06:59.211 --> 07:01.202
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

07:08.178 --> 07:11.591
Are you okay? You usually
make cappuccinos blindfolded.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.221
Clark, hey.

07:13.391 --> 07:17.259
Uh, yeah, I just didn't get
my full seven hours of sleep last night.

07:18.772 --> 07:21.104
And judging from the look on your face...

07:21.274 --> 07:23.765
...you didn't come here
to join me for pancakes.

07:23.944 --> 07:26.276
Tess named Davis the serial killer.

07:27.155 --> 07:30.363
She devoted the whole front page
of today's paper to the story.

07:34.204 --> 07:36.115
Headlines can't hurt Davis
now that he's dead.

07:36.289 --> 07:40.328
That's the thing, Chloe. I'm starting
to believe that Davis is still alive.

07:41.586 --> 07:45.170
Come on, Clark.
We both watched him die.

07:45.340 --> 07:46.705
Oliver buried the body.

07:46.883 --> 07:48.043
But it says in this article...

07:48.218 --> 07:52.052
...they found one of Bruno Mannheim's
thugs in a dumpster, torn apart...

07:52.222 --> 07:55.430
...the same way that Doomsday
dismembered his victims.

07:55.725 --> 07:57.556
That body was probably there for weeks.

07:58.562 --> 08:00.723
The murder happened after Davis died.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.641
I love a good ghost story
as much as the next girl.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.901
There has to be
a more logical explanation...

08:08.071 --> 08:10.687
...than the resurrection
of an alien monster.

08:10.866 --> 08:12.902
There could be a copycat killer.

08:13.743 --> 08:15.734
Chloe, he's come back
from the dead before.

08:17.038 --> 08:19.074
Not from meteor rock.

08:22.836 --> 08:25.418
Look, Clark,
I understand why you're paranoid.

08:25.589 --> 08:27.420
Davis was sent here to kill you.

08:27.591 --> 08:30.378
That would make anyone believe
there were monsters under their bed.

08:33.180 --> 08:35.171
That doesn't change the fact
Davis is a murderer.

08:35.557 --> 08:38.799
But, Clark, Davis is dead.

08:38.977 --> 08:42.970
And the only thing that's keeping him alive
in your mind is fear.

08:43.732 --> 08:44.767
Let him go.

08:55.785 --> 08:57.070
LuthorCorp is going green.

08:57.245 --> 09:01.784
I don't want the investors to think we're
wasting money on hemp bracelets, so....

09:01.958 --> 09:05.075
We could send some cameras
into the geothermal energy facility.

09:05.253 --> 09:08.120
It's innovative. It's proﬁtable.

09:08.298 --> 09:11.756
Okay. Perfect.
Call Tess, arrange a press release.

09:11.927 --> 09:14.760
Nothing screams "photo op"
like a 10-mile hole in the ground.

09:14.930 --> 09:15.965
[JIMMY CLEARS THROAT]

09:18.725 --> 09:21.808
Hey, Oliver,
um, can we talk for a quick sec?

09:21.978 --> 09:23.809
Hey, Jimmy, uh...

09:23.980 --> 09:26.141
...not the greatest time
right now, actually.

09:26.650 --> 09:28.390
I wouldn't ask if it wasn't important.

09:29.110 --> 09:31.237
Okay. All right.

09:31.404 --> 09:33.315
Gentlemen, excuse me.

09:33.490 --> 09:34.821
Thank you.

09:34.991 --> 09:36.731
I'm sorry to barge in on your lunch--

09:36.910 --> 09:40.323
Jimmy, listen. Those guys aren't
my frat brothers. I'm here on business.

09:40.497 --> 09:41.486
Yeah. I know. I know.

09:41.665 --> 09:43.781
Uh. Real quick.

09:43.959 --> 09:47.167
l was hoping that you could
spot me 600 bucks, stat.

09:47.337 --> 09:49.794
A mechanic called a code blue
on my alternator.

09:49.965 --> 09:52.798
You work here. What are they
paying you in, Shirley Temples?

09:53.718 --> 09:56.004
They, uh— They let me go.

09:56.179 --> 09:59.012
Cutbacks. I mean, you know how that is.

10:00.225 --> 10:01.715
I do.

10:02.185 --> 10:05.848
That's why I'm pretty sure
it's not your car that needs the ﬁx, buddy.

10:08.400 --> 10:10.482
You think that I'm lying?

10:10.735 --> 10:12.851
I got three bus transfers to prove it.

10:14.281 --> 10:16.567
Listen, I know a really great place
you can go to.

10:21.288 --> 10:24.325
And if you're worried about paying
for your treatment, don't.

10:24.833 --> 10:26.619
I can take care of that for you, okay?

10:28.545 --> 10:29.876
Great.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.253
You gonna drive me there too?

10:32.841 --> 10:34.797
Because my car doesn't work.

10:35.635 --> 10:36.715
OLIVER:
All right, hey.

10:39.556 --> 10:43.094
This road that you're on, man,
it is lonely, all right?

10:43.893 --> 10:47.021
Now, if you need someone to talk to,
if you need a friend...

10:48.189 --> 10:50.225
...then I'm that guy, but, uh...

10:52.027 --> 10:53.983
...l'm not gonna give you
any money for drugs.

10:56.489 --> 11:00.232
You know, I thought after everything
that happened that we could be friends.

11:01.411 --> 11:04.198
But seeing that you don't trust me,
I guess not.

11:14.758 --> 11:17.170
You've been caring for Davis Bloome
in your basement?

11:19.596 --> 11:20.756
Who else knows about this?

11:21.723 --> 11:23.259
No one.

11:23.641 --> 11:28.135
Not even Oliver. And I came to you directly
because he can't be trusted.

11:29.105 --> 11:32.689
Chloe, he created our organization
to help with exactly this kind of problem.

11:36.196 --> 11:37.936
Oliver killed Lex Luthor.

11:39.783 --> 11:43.947
And the stakes are too high to have
someone involved who can't think clearly.

11:44.954 --> 11:48.287
WebMD doesn't exactly have
a lot of intergalactic infections.

11:48.458 --> 11:51.120
You are the only person
that I could turn to for a cure.

11:54.506 --> 11:56.872
No. I'm glad that you came to me.

11:57.050 --> 12:01.293
But there's only so much I can do
with a few cells.

12:01.471 --> 12:03.803
You have his DNA.
What more do you need?

12:03.973 --> 12:05.133
The subject in person.

12:08.812 --> 12:09.892
That's not gonna happen.

12:14.609 --> 12:16.816
I can run some preliminary tests
on the saliva.

12:20.657 --> 12:22.113
But, Chloe, are—?

12:22.283 --> 12:24.615
Are you sure this is something
you wanna take on alone?

12:26.454 --> 12:29.662
I'll be ﬁne.
Call me when you get the results.

12:38.466 --> 12:39.797
[GASPS]

12:39.968 --> 12:42.175
-Who was that?
-Davis, you shouldn't be outside.

12:42.345 --> 12:44.757
What's going on?
Look at me. It's ﬁne, okay?

12:44.931 --> 12:46.546
Calm down. It's just a friend.

12:46.724 --> 12:50.308
Now, you know you're not supposed
to be out the house. What's happening?

12:52.272 --> 12:55.014
Nothing helps.
I tried looking at photos of you.

12:55.191 --> 12:57.978
I tried holding strands of your hair.
None of it works.

12:58.403 --> 13:03.693
This thing inside me starts to claw
its way out as soon as you leave.

13:04.659 --> 13:06.320
Chloe...

13:07.370 --> 13:09.110
...I can't be away from you now.

13:16.588 --> 13:20.001
CHLOE: You are now Metropolis'
own Cornﬁeld Killer.

13:20.175 --> 13:22.837
I didn't tell you
because I didn't want to upset you...

13:23.011 --> 13:27.380
...but the police are hunting for you
as we speak.

13:27.891 --> 13:30.598
And by accepting your help,
I put you in their crosshairs.

13:30.768 --> 13:34.056
Only if someone ﬁnds you.
Which they won't. I won't let that happen.

13:34.230 --> 13:36.972
Well, what about when the cops ﬁnd you?
What then?

13:37.734 --> 13:38.894
Then we leave.

13:46.117 --> 13:48.199
We load up the car and never look back.

13:54.417 --> 13:58.751
You've done more for me in a few weeks
than anyone's done in my entire life...

13:58.922 --> 14:01.004
...but I can't ask you
to run away with me.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.420
It's a good thing
you're not the one asking.

14:21.277 --> 14:25.941
You wouldn't be able to say goodbye
to anyone. Not even Clark.

14:26.115 --> 14:28.777
Can you do that?

14:29.452 --> 14:34.116
Can you honestly tell me that I am
the most important person in your life?

14:39.045 --> 14:40.581
Davis...

14:43.633 --> 14:45.715
...I would do anything for you.

14:55.103 --> 14:57.890
Well, then maybe
this is our chance to start over.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.144
Let's leave Smallville.

15:02.485 --> 15:03.565
Okay.

15:06.614 --> 15:08.479
So this is actually happening.

15:08.658 --> 15:09.647
[SIGHS]

15:09.826 --> 15:13.739
Um, I just need to close a few accounts
and dead-end some paper trails ﬁrst.

15:13.913 --> 15:15.744
We can be on the road by sundown.

15:17.292 --> 15:18.657
Chloe...

15:21.838 --> 15:23.749
...I don't know where I'd be without you.

15:47.405 --> 15:50.488
Oliver. I checked the quarry
where you said you buried Davis.

15:50.658 --> 15:52.819
-He's not there.
-Your vision must be blurry.

15:52.994 --> 15:56.111
l buried that body myself.
Still have the dirt under my ﬁngernails.

15:56.289 --> 15:59.031
I saw the grave. It's empty.

15:59.834 --> 16:02.826
-Why would someone move the body?
-I don't think anyone moved it.

16:03.004 --> 16:04.915
It doesn't look like anyone
dug into the ground.

16:05.089 --> 16:08.172
It looks like something
clawed its way out.

16:09.719 --> 16:11.175
Then that thing's still alive.

16:11.346 --> 16:13.678
It went after Chloe before.
It may try again.

16:14.140 --> 16:15.380
Have you warned her yet?

16:16.225 --> 16:18.477
She thinks I'm being paranoid.

16:19.520 --> 16:21.056
Paranoid?

16:21.397 --> 16:22.978
She knows he's obsessed with her?

16:23.149 --> 16:25.765
Which is why I need you to ﬁnd her,
take her someplace safe.

16:25.943 --> 16:28.730
I need to head to the Fortress
to send Doomsday to a place...

16:28.905 --> 16:30.896
...he can't hurt anyone again.

16:32.742 --> 16:34.152
No need to pack your parka.

16:34.327 --> 16:36.409
I can tell you how to conquer the beast.

16:38.164 --> 16:40.200
Kick his ass, Clark.

16:40.625 --> 16:43.708
Get this thing out of our lives
once and for all.

16:43.878 --> 16:45.584
You want me to kill him.

16:47.298 --> 16:48.413
No.

16:48.591 --> 16:51.674
I need you to kill him. We all do.
You're the only one who can.

16:51.844 --> 16:54.381
That doesn't make it right.
I'd still be taking a life.

16:54.555 --> 16:56.716
You'd be saving thousands, Clark.

16:57.684 --> 17:02.053
The only way any of us are gonna be safe
again is if Doomsday is destroyed. For good.

17:05.608 --> 17:08.691
Just please, take care of Chloe.

17:17.870 --> 17:20.953
I'm down to my last card, Emil,
and I really don't wanna play it.

17:21.124 --> 17:23.490
So please take another look
at the samples.

17:23.668 --> 17:25.875
There has to be a cure.

17:26.212 --> 17:29.796
His nuclei are in a constant state
of mutation.

17:29.966 --> 17:33.458
I tried to destroy a cell
and somehow it got stronger.

17:34.262 --> 17:37.629
You wanted to see him in person.
How about I bring him to your lab?

17:37.807 --> 17:40.970
-I don't want him anywhere near me.
-Look, he's not always a monster.

17:41.144 --> 17:43.806
I mean, something is keeping him
from transforming.

17:45.231 --> 17:46.971
Well, sometimes...

17:47.150 --> 17:51.143
...dramatic changes to the body
are caused by intense emotions.

17:51.320 --> 17:53.982
Love, hate...

17:54.907 --> 17:56.568
...obsession.

18:00.997 --> 18:04.489
Which is why my presence
stops him from morphing.

18:06.294 --> 18:09.457
Chloe, this creature puts us all in danger.

18:09.630 --> 18:11.791
We need to warn people.

18:12.175 --> 18:13.915
You don't wanna do that.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.708
You betray me, you betray Davis.

18:15.887 --> 18:18.344
And you sure as hell
don't wanna be on his bad side.

18:19.348 --> 18:20.679
Fine.

18:21.893 --> 18:25.181
But if you do have this power over him,
then it's all on you.

18:25.646 --> 18:27.307
You're the only cure.

18:32.236 --> 18:33.692
[CLARK APPROACHES]

18:35.615 --> 18:37.025
Were you talking to someone?

18:37.909 --> 18:40.025
Just one of my patients.

18:41.204 --> 18:42.694
Have you heard from Oliver?

18:43.164 --> 18:46.656
Not since he asked me to hack
into a stream of transmissions from Tehran.

18:46.834 --> 18:51.453
And considering the fact
that, uh, Farsi isn't exactly my strong suit...

18:51.631 --> 18:53.963
...I should probably
get back to translating.

18:54.133 --> 18:56.294
Chloe, Davis is alive.

18:57.470 --> 18:59.586
l have proof and I need to ﬁnd him.

18:59.764 --> 19:02.380
I'm sure that when he resurfaces,
we'll hear about it.

19:03.059 --> 19:06.176
He has a habit of crashing his way
onto the 6:00 news.

19:06.354 --> 19:09.016
Well, I intend to ﬁnd him and bring him
to the Fortress.

19:09.190 --> 19:10.930
I got a faint signal from the console.

19:11.108 --> 19:13.645
I found the crystal that Brainiac
used to release Zod.

19:13.820 --> 19:18.564
Okay, putting aside my serious distrust
of all things Brainiac...

19:18.741 --> 19:20.242
...how is the crystal gonna help?

19:20.785 --> 19:23.151
It's gonna open up a portal
to the Phantom Zone.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.741
Clark, you can't send Davis there.

19:27.208 --> 19:29.915
He has killed over 50 people.
He put Jimmy in the hospital.

19:30.086 --> 19:33.499
-There's nothing more I can do for him.
-No, I'm talking about you.

19:33.673 --> 19:36.415
I mean, what if when you open the portal
it sucks you in?

19:36.884 --> 19:40.797
You once told me if there was no other
choice, put the good of the world ﬁrst.

19:40.972 --> 19:42.428
Exactly.

19:42.598 --> 19:44.884
And losing you is not good for the world.

19:45.059 --> 19:47.266
It's a risk I have to take.

19:51.440 --> 19:53.305
Okay, then maybe I can help.

19:53.484 --> 19:57.898
I've been hearing about a string
of suspicious murders in Alaska.

19:58.072 --> 20:00.939
I didn't pay much attention.
They weren't trademark Doomsday--

20:01.117 --> 20:04.701
-lt's okay. It's a lead. I'll ﬁnd him.
-Hey, Clark.

20:06.372 --> 20:07.828
Good luck.

20:27.727 --> 20:29.763
[CLANGING NEARBY]

20:33.649 --> 20:35.230
[GASPS]

20:36.152 --> 20:38.609
So you're stealing money
from Chloe now.

20:38.779 --> 20:40.986
I guess your car really does need
those repairs.

20:42.909 --> 20:44.991
It's just a loan.

20:45.578 --> 20:46.909
I'm gonna pay it back.

20:47.705 --> 20:49.115
[GRUNTS]

20:54.253 --> 20:56.084
Holy--

21:01.010 --> 21:02.341
[GRUNTS]

21:03.721 --> 21:05.427
[MOANS]

21:12.063 --> 21:14.520
Oh, what the hell.

21:18.778 --> 21:21.440
Hey, Jimmy. Hey.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.320
[HANDCUFF CLANGS]

21:24.909 --> 21:26.365
Hey. You okay?

21:26.535 --> 21:28.196
[PANTS]

21:29.497 --> 21:32.739
Aside from being snatched
by a crazed serial killer...

21:34.377 --> 21:35.708
...yeah, I'm great.

21:36.420 --> 21:38.035
Any idea who did this?

21:39.298 --> 21:41.710
Not to sound like a broken record,
but it was Davis Bloome.

21:46.973 --> 21:48.759
Where the hell are we?

21:49.016 --> 21:51.223
Looks like the Talon basement.

21:52.520 --> 21:54.806
My God. What's he done with Chloe?

21:55.815 --> 21:58.227
DAVIS:
I'd never hurt Chloe.

22:01.362 --> 22:02.977
She, uh....

22:03.572 --> 22:05.483
She saved me.

22:05.658 --> 22:07.489
[LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY]

22:07.660 --> 22:08.900
No way.

22:09.078 --> 22:12.241
Chloe might be a sucker for the strange,
but she's not crazy.

22:12.415 --> 22:14.701
Bit of advice...

22:15.042 --> 22:17.875
...you really don't want to upset me
right now.

22:19.005 --> 22:20.586
OLIVER:
Yeah, trust me, I know.

22:20.756 --> 22:22.087
I've seen your horns.

22:23.175 --> 22:26.588
You give a whole new meaning
to the term "bridezilla." Ha, ha.

22:32.810 --> 22:35.267
You're the beast.

22:39.859 --> 22:41.065
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

22:44.488 --> 22:47.104
Hey, Davis. It's me.
I'm just on my way home right now.

22:47.283 --> 22:49.194
Chloe, hurry. I can feel myself changing.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.609
-Please get back and stop it.
-Chloe, stay away!

22:54.957 --> 22:56.413
Is there someone there with you?

22:57.126 --> 22:59.287
Some guys broke into your apartment.

22:59.462 --> 23:00.451
I 'rn holding them here.

23:00.629 --> 23:02.290
Why did you leave the basement?

23:02.465 --> 23:04.205
Because I thought you were in danger.

23:05.009 --> 23:10.299
Okay, you trust me, right?
So trust me on this and let them go.

23:10.473 --> 23:13.135
As soon as we're out of Smallville.

23:14.477 --> 23:17.310
Just come home, Chloe. Hurry.

23:17.480 --> 23:19.721
I'll be there as soon as I can.

23:30.826 --> 23:33.112
JIMMY:
Why did you do it?

23:38.709 --> 23:40.449
Come on.

23:41.003 --> 23:43.710
Every killer's got a sob story.

23:44.840 --> 23:48.332
You know,
I hear that a unhappy childhood, that's—

23:48.511 --> 23:50.047
That's pretty popular.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.261
You wouldn't understand.

23:52.431 --> 23:53.887
[JIMMY LAUGHS]

23:54.517 --> 23:56.758
Of course not. Because you, uh....

23:56.936 --> 23:59.769
You brooding types,
you guys are all so complicated.

24:00.856 --> 24:03.393
-Come on, man. Chill out.
-No!

24:03.567 --> 24:05.307
No, that monster destroyed my life...

24:05.486 --> 24:08.023
...and brainwashed Chloe,
and he's trying to ruin hers too.

24:08.197 --> 24:11.030
You have no idea what Chloe wants.
We have to be together.

24:11.200 --> 24:12.531
OLIVER:
Davis? Hey.

24:12.701 --> 24:16.159
Hey, man. Look, I know what it's like
to jones after a girl, really I do.

24:16.330 --> 24:19.447
But you can hold on a bit longer.
You have to. Chloe's on her way.

24:19.625 --> 24:21.035
Oh, I hope so.

24:21.210 --> 24:23.292
I really do. Because if she's not...

24:23.462 --> 24:27.296
...the only way that I can control myself
is if I kill one of you.

24:31.095 --> 24:33.256
Then kill me.

24:34.056 --> 24:37.514
Because you've taken everything from me.
All that's left is scar tissue.

24:39.854 --> 24:40.889
OLIVER:
Jimmy.

24:41.063 --> 24:42.223
Jimmy, that's enough.

24:44.692 --> 24:47.559
What are you, anyways?
Because you're sure as hell not human.

24:47.736 --> 24:50.068
Stop talking.

24:51.782 --> 24:53.522
[PANTS]

25:00.457 --> 25:03.585
Do you really think
that Chloe could ever love you?

25:05.171 --> 25:07.628
Whatever lies that you told her...

25:08.257 --> 25:11.044
...she's gonna ﬁnd out the truth eventually.
And when she does--

25:11.218 --> 25:13.083
[ROARS]

25:20.186 --> 25:21.767
Davis. Davis!

25:22.605 --> 25:24.846
Chloe's never gonna forgive you for that.
You understand?

25:25.024 --> 25:26.434
[JIMMY GROANS]

25:27.651 --> 25:29.152
OLIVER:
Please.

25:29.320 --> 25:31.276
Please.

25:32.323 --> 25:35.281
[DAVIS PANTS]

25:35.451 --> 25:37.112
DAVIS:
You're right.

25:39.121 --> 25:41.737
You mean too much to Chloe.

25:54.595 --> 25:55.960
It has to be you.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.924
Davis.

26:01.477 --> 26:03.934
Sometimes the monster
really does get the girl.

26:04.104 --> 26:05.765
I'm
sorry

26:09.902 --> 26:11.642
Chloe!

26:19.453 --> 26:20.989
Chloe?

26:25.834 --> 26:29.452
OLIVER:
No. No. Davis.

26:30.339 --> 26:31.670
Fight it.

26:32.007 --> 26:33.543
Davis, don't do this.

26:33.717 --> 26:35.969
-No. You don't have to do this.
-Oliver.

26:39.682 --> 26:42.014
Where's Chloe?

26:42.184 --> 26:44.675
What are you gonna do to me, Clark?

27:20.472 --> 27:22.508
Oh, my God.

27:24.310 --> 27:26.392
Was Davis was holding Jimmy
in the basement?

27:26.770 --> 27:28.510
They're lucky to be alive.

27:32.901 --> 27:34.892
Jimmy, I'm so sorry.

27:41.827 --> 27:44.239
Whatever you do, Chloe...

27:45.080 --> 27:48.038
-...you stay away from that monster.
-Let's go.

27:53.922 --> 27:56.379
You know, Chloe,
I thought about calling the police.

27:56.550 --> 27:58.757
I ﬁgured I'd give you a chance
to explain...

27:58.927 --> 28:01.839
...before I let them haul you to prison
for harboring a killer.

28:02.014 --> 28:04.221
I shouldn't have left Davis here alone.

28:04.391 --> 28:06.427
This would never have happened
if I was here.

28:06.602 --> 28:08.763
This is all my fault.

28:11.231 --> 28:13.608
When did you become
one of the bad guys, huh?

28:15.778 --> 28:19.737
For whatever reason,
I calm the beast inside him. He needed me.

28:19.907 --> 28:21.738
He needed you.

28:23.327 --> 28:26.444
So the needs of the Cornﬁeld Killer
outweigh the needs of the world?

28:26.622 --> 28:28.112
-lt's complicated—
-Complicated.

28:28.290 --> 28:30.781
Same thing
your psychopathic boyfriend told me.

28:30.959 --> 28:34.872
Look, either I keep him with me
or let innocent people die.

28:35.047 --> 28:36.537
Come on.

28:37.257 --> 28:40.420
Chloe, if you believed that,
you would've handled things differently.

28:40.594 --> 28:43.552
Instead what do you do?
You ﬂuff his pillow, rock him to sleep.

28:43.722 --> 28:45.963
I understand what it looked like
from the outside.

28:46.141 --> 28:48.803
But trust me,
I had the whole thing under control—

28:48.977 --> 28:51.889
You didn't have anything under control.
Speaking as Davis' next victim...

28:52.064 --> 28:55.306
...I can tell you,
your plan was seriously ﬂawed.

29:01.115 --> 29:04.152
How did you think
this was gonna end, Chloe?

29:07.162 --> 29:09.448
-l'll ﬁnd him, okay? I'll ﬁx this.
OLIVER: No.

29:10.332 --> 29:11.492
You won't.

29:14.211 --> 29:17.248
I think you've done enough.
We'll let Clark handle it from here.

29:17.423 --> 29:21.007
Wait, Oliver, where is Clark?

29:23.679 --> 29:25.795
Oh, he took Davis.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.351
He's ﬁnally gonna ﬁnish this.

29:49.455 --> 29:51.036
[G ROWLS]

29:51.206 --> 29:56.371
I don't care if this place
trapped me once before.

29:56.545 --> 29:59.457
You wanna throw down with me?
Good luck.

29:59.631 --> 30:03.920
I didn't come here looking for a ﬁght.
This Fortress can help you.

30:05.053 --> 30:06.884
It's all that's left of our planet.

30:11.018 --> 30:13.009
How did a piece of Krypton get here?

30:13.187 --> 30:16.850
My father created it
using Kryptonian technology.

30:17.274 --> 30:20.482
It will send you to a world
where you don't have to hide who you are.

30:22.571 --> 30:25.028
A world without Chloe?

30:32.623 --> 30:36.241
Well, you better have a plan B,
because I'm not losing her.

30:36.418 --> 30:38.875
If you truly cared about her,
you would let her go.

30:40.422 --> 30:42.128
You got it all wrong, Clark.

30:42.299 --> 30:44.255
She chose to protect me.

30:44.426 --> 30:46.883
It was her idea
for us to leave Smallville forever.

30:47.054 --> 30:49.090
Chloe would have done that for anyone.

30:49.264 --> 30:52.006
She believes in second chances.

30:53.977 --> 30:55.933
She doesn't
actually have feelings for you.

30:56.104 --> 30:58.937
Why, because of what I am?

30:59.107 --> 31:04.352
I didn't want this, Clark.
I even killed myself to try escape this life.

31:04.530 --> 31:08.569
But the darkness,
it doesn't come out when Chloe's around.

31:08.742 --> 31:10.278
She makes me...

31:11.578 --> 31:13.284
...human.

31:21.755 --> 31:23.791
What happens when that changes?

31:25.133 --> 31:26.873
It won't.

31:28.554 --> 31:30.340
She is my chance to be happy.

31:30.514 --> 31:32.800
Why can't my Kryptonian brother
let me have that?

31:33.559 --> 31:35.470
I'm sorry, Davis. I was wrong.

31:35.644 --> 31:37.635
We're not brothers.

31:39.481 --> 31:41.642
Clark.

31:57.207 --> 31:59.584
I don't wanna hurt you, Davis.

32:00.210 --> 32:02.496
Don't worry, you can't.

32:34.286 --> 32:37.153
If I go, I'm taking you with me.

32:56.767 --> 32:58.052
Chloe?

32:58.226 --> 32:59.386
What are you doing?

32:59.853 --> 33:01.013
I can't let you do this.

33:06.693 --> 33:09.685
This is the right choice, Chloe, trust me.

33:11.406 --> 33:12.395
Trust you?

33:13.075 --> 33:15.031
The only reason why you won't kill him...

33:15.202 --> 33:17.568
...is because you don't want blood
on your hands.

33:17.746 --> 33:22.410
I can't believe you were willing to force him
into a life of hell for all of eternity.

33:23.502 --> 33:25.333
Clark.

33:25.962 --> 33:30.126
I know you better than anyone.
I can't let you do this.

33:30.300 --> 33:33.542
You would never forgive yourself
for giving up on him.

34:10.048 --> 34:12.084
Tell me your search team
has a read on that beast.

34:13.719 --> 34:16.301
l have people on every continent,
Jimmy, but so far, no.

34:16.471 --> 34:17.460
No castle to storm.

34:18.974 --> 34:20.930
Sorry.

34:22.894 --> 34:27.103
I'm not sure the beast you need to be
ﬁghting is out there. I think maybe, uh....

34:27.274 --> 34:28.389
Maybe it's in here.

34:30.444 --> 34:34.403
Look, if this is another attempt
to turn me into the poster boy for rehab...

34:34.573 --> 34:37.280
...cancel the photo shoot,
because I'm not interested.

34:37.451 --> 34:39.567
I didn't call you here for a lecture.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.615
Just this.

34:42.789 --> 34:45.326
It's the, uh, money you asked for.

34:45.500 --> 34:47.286
For your car.

34:53.675 --> 34:54.755
Forget it.

34:54.926 --> 34:56.837
I don't— I don't need your handout.

34:57.012 --> 34:59.128
This is not a handout. It's your paycheck.

34:59.306 --> 35:02.423
Oh, let me guess.
It's got 12 steps attached to it.

35:02.976 --> 35:04.011
[CH UCKLES]

35:04.186 --> 35:08.304
Well, only if you decide not to take
the elevator to your ofﬁce.

35:08.482 --> 35:13.647
Truth is, there's an opening on my staff,
and something tells me you'd be perfect.

35:15.322 --> 35:19.031
I ran a little background check.
It seems to me there's more to your story...

35:19.201 --> 35:21.192
...than, uh,
you write on your cover letter.

35:21.369 --> 35:23.701
Unfortunately, what you see
is what you get.

35:23.872 --> 35:26.113
I'm a mediocre
photographer-turned-bartender.

35:26.291 --> 35:29.374
I don't remember seeing
a posting for that on CareerBuilder.com.

35:31.713 --> 35:34.204
I don't know. Everybody knows
you take great action shots.

35:34.883 --> 35:38.000
What I didn't realize until recently...

35:38.178 --> 35:41.796
...was when called upon,
you're pretty damn good in action as well.

35:44.184 --> 35:46.516
You make it sound
like I'm some kind of hero.

35:50.273 --> 35:51.683
Trust me, I'm not.

35:54.277 --> 35:56.393
I wouldn't be so sure.

35:57.113 --> 36:00.071
You ﬁgured out Davis Bloome's secret
before any of us did.

36:00.242 --> 36:02.153
You took on the beast all by yourself.

36:02.327 --> 36:04.409
That takes guts.

36:05.747 --> 36:07.908
You got good instincts, Jimmy.

36:08.083 --> 36:10.074
-That's enough for me.
-Yeah.

36:10.877 --> 36:14.495
Thanks to those instincts,
my life is really awesome these days.

36:16.258 --> 36:18.874
Well, if you don't like it, change it.

36:21.513 --> 36:24.095
Which you start by accepting my offer.

36:25.809 --> 36:26.844
What's the catch?

36:27.018 --> 36:28.053
[OLIVER CHUCKLES]

36:28.228 --> 36:32.096
No, no, no catch. No catch, just work.
Uh, and a lot of it. It's a full-time gig.

36:34.442 --> 36:35.602
What do you say?

36:56.798 --> 36:58.459
[DOOR OPENS]

37:07.601 --> 37:10.559
If you're looking for Chloe,
you're wasting your time, Clark.

37:10.729 --> 37:13.311
But I guess that's what you do best,
isn't it?

37:16.359 --> 37:19.351
She's gone, man.
She doesn't wanna be found.

37:19.529 --> 37:22.487
If there's anyone who can make
themselves invisible, it's Chloe.

37:23.658 --> 37:24.864
Davis must have done something.

37:25.035 --> 37:27.151
Chloe would never lie
if she weren't trapped.

37:27.329 --> 37:29.911
Either that or she can't resist
tall, dark and Doomsday.

37:30.081 --> 37:32.572
Besides, Davis isn't a monster
when he's around her.

37:32.751 --> 37:36.744
-He's got real feelings for her.
-Whatever his feelings are for her...

37:37.422 --> 37:39.162
...Chloe would never care about him.

37:41.217 --> 37:43.674
Clark, she sent you
on a wild-goose chase to Alaska...

37:43.845 --> 37:46.803
...when she was hiding
that psycho-killer in the basement.

37:48.141 --> 37:51.975
Take it from a guy who spent $10 billion
on a merger with the girl that got away.

37:52.145 --> 37:54.010
You don't always choose
who you fall for.

37:54.189 --> 37:57.522
The Chloe you're talking about
does not exist.

37:57.943 --> 38:00.855
She'd never choose Davis
over her friends.

38:04.366 --> 38:06.823
Well, people change, Clark.

38:07.744 --> 38:09.860
Maybe it's time you did too.

38:12.582 --> 38:15.244
You should have killed that thing
when you had the chance.

38:25.470 --> 38:28.257
Clark, I know
you wanna save everybody...

38:30.100 --> 38:33.137
...but eventually you're gonna
have to make the tough decisions.

38:36.064 --> 38:38.100
That's what heroes do.

39:02.007 --> 39:03.998
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

39:11.641 --> 39:13.256
CLARK [OVER PHONE]:
Who is this?

39:14.060 --> 39:17.018
Clark, it's Chloe.
I just wanted to let you know that I'm okay.

39:17.188 --> 39:18.394
Chloe.

39:18.565 --> 39:19.680
Where are you?

39:19.858 --> 39:22.941
Davis and l are gone,
but please don't try and ﬁnd us, okay?

39:24.446 --> 39:27.483
You think you're safe, but you aren't.
You are not safe with him.

39:27.657 --> 39:29.943
I'm sure everyone's ﬁtting me
for a straitjacket.

39:30.118 --> 39:32.359
But, Clark, I do know what I'm doing.

39:32.537 --> 39:35.620
I knew if I told you sooner
you would've found a way to stop me.

39:38.084 --> 39:43.704
Look, everything I've ever done,
right or wrong, I did for you.

39:43.882 --> 39:45.838
By running away?

39:46.092 --> 39:49.550
Admit it. You have feelings for Davis.
That's why you're protecting him.

39:50.138 --> 39:51.969
Clark, I'm protecting you.

39:53.266 --> 39:54.597
[OVER PHONE]
I meant what I said.

39:55.143 --> 39:58.476
Condemning Davis to a life as that monster
is worse than killing him.

39:58.646 --> 39:59.806
CLARK:
What about you, Chloe?

40:01.107 --> 40:04.645
I'm gonna spend every second looking
for you. I will ﬁnd a way to save you.

40:05.195 --> 40:09.313
Clark, you're not here to save one person,
you're here to save all of us.

40:10.784 --> 40:13.491
And you think sacriﬁcing yourself
will help me do that.

40:16.664 --> 40:18.700
Chloe, you're wrong.

40:19.334 --> 40:20.414
You're wrong, Chloe.

40:20.585 --> 40:22.997
CHLOE: I must have thrown
a million green rocks away...

40:23.171 --> 40:25.207
...and I have never really saved you.

40:27.342 --> 40:29.333
Now I can.

40:31.513 --> 40:35.677
Chloe, listen to me. This is your life
that we're talking about. Don't do this.

40:39.395 --> 40:40.680
Clark...

40:40.855 --> 40:43.267
...if there's one lesson
I've learned from you...

40:43.441 --> 40:47.480
...it's that choosing the greater good
is never a sacriﬁce.

40:48.113 --> 40:49.603
CLARK [OVER PHONE]:
Chloe?

40:49.781 --> 40:51.396
Chloe!

40:51.574 --> 40:52.905
[GRUNTS]

41:09.843 --> 41:13.131
You said that, uh, road trips
give you a sweet tooth, so....

41:15.598 --> 41:17.554
Thank you.

41:17.725 --> 41:20.467
We better get moving
if we wanna hit the border by morning.

41:22.564 --> 41:23.974
Let's disappear.

42:21.331 --> 42:23.322
[ENGLISH SDH]
